{
  "text": "In addition, there is a report of a patient who underwent hemodialysis and developed sepsis caused by a Corynebacterium sp. [CITATION_1] . As the same type of bacteria was detected by the catheter tip culture, the cervical catheter was withdrawn during the hemodialysis, as it was presumed to be the port of entry in this case.",
